This is a missed-optimization in SROA.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
declare void @use.i32(i32)

define void @load_dyn_offset(ptr %ary) {
  %a = alloca { i64, [4 x i32] }, align 8
  store i64 0, ptr %a, align 4
  %gep = getelementptr i8, ptr %a, i64 8
  call void @llvm.memcpy.p0.p0.i64(ptr %gep, ptr %ary, i64 16, i1 false)
  br label %loop

loop:                                             ; preds = %loop, %0
  %i = load i64, ptr %a, align 4
  %i.next = add i64 %i, 1
  store i64 %i.next, ptr %a, align 4
  %gep.i = getelementptr i32, ptr %gep, i64 %i
  %val = load i32, ptr %gep.i, align 4
  call void @use.i32(i32 %val)
  %cmp = icmp eq i64 %i.next, 6
  br i1 %cmp, label %exit, label %loop

exit:                                             ; preds = %loop
  ret void
}

; Function Attrs: nocallback nofree nounwind willreturn memory(argmem: readwrite)
declare void @llvm.memcpy.p0.p0.i64(ptr noalias nocapture writeonly, ptr noalias nocapture readonly, i64, i1 immarg) #0

attributes #0 = { nocallback nofree nounwind willreturn memory(argmem: readwrite) }

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
